  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 255596ce6b91ac640b392e20dd4f8a9e, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Day of Judgment on Judah'
      title: Day of Judgment on Judah
      number: 1
      content: '  The word of the Lord which came to Zephaniah the son of Cushi,
        the son of Gedaliah, the son of Amariah, the son of Hezekiah, in the days
        of Josiah the son of Amon, king of Judah:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CI will completely consume and sweep away all thingsFrom the
        face of the earth [in judgment],\u201D says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CI will consume and sweep away man and beast;I will consume
        and sweep away the birds of the airAnd the fish of the sea,And the stumbling
        blocks (idols) along with the wicked;And I will cut off and destroy man from
        the face of the earth,\u201D declares the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CI will also stretch out My hand [in judgment] against JudahAnd
        against all the inhabitants of Jerusalem.And I will cut off and destroy the
        remnant of Baal from this place,And the names and remembrance of the idolatrous
        priests along with the [false] priests,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And those who bow down and worship the host of heaven [the sun, the
        moon, and the stars] on their housetopsAnd those who bow down and swear [oaths]
        to [and pretend to worship] the Lord and [yet also] swear by [the pagan god
        called] Milcom [god of the Ammonites],  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And those who have turned back from following the Lord,And those
        who have not sought the Lord [as their most important need] or inquired of
        Him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '[Hush!] Be silent before the Lord God [there is no acceptable excuse
        to offer]!For the day [of the vengeance] of the Lord is near,For the Lord
        has prepared a sacrifice (Judah),He has set apart [for His use] those who
        have accepted His invitation [the Chaldeans who rule Babylon].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CThen it will come about on the day of the Lord\u2019s sacrificeThat
        I will punish the princes and the king\u2019s sonsAnd all who are clothed
        in [lavish] foreign apparel [reflecting their paganism].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "On that day I will also punish all those who leap over the temple
        threshold,Who fill their [pagan] lord\u2019s temple with violence and deceit.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "On that day,\u201D declares the Lord,\u201CThere will be the sound
        of crying from the Fish (Damascus) Gate [in the northern wall of Jerusalem
        where invaders enter]And wailing from the Second Quarter [of the city],And
        a loud crash from the hills.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Wail [in anguish], you inhabitants of the Mortar (Valley of Siloam),For
        all the merchants of Canaan will be silenced and destroyed;All who weigh
        out silver will be cut off.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "It will come about at that timeThat I will search Jerusalem with
        lampsAnd I will punish the menWho [like old wine] are stagnant in spirit,Who
        say in their hearts,\u2018The Lord will not do good, nor will He do evil.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Furthermore, their wealth will become plunderAnd their houses a desolation.Yes,
        they will build houses but not live in them,And plant vineyards but not drink
        their wine.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The great [judgment] day of the Lord is near,Near and coming very
        quickly.Listen! The [voice of the] day of the Lord!The warrior cries out
        bitterly [unable to fight or to flee].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'That day is a day of [the outpouring of the] wrath [of God],A day
        of trouble and distress,A day of destruction and devastation,A day of darkness
        and gloom,A day of clouds and thick darkness,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'A day of trumpet and the battle cry [of invaders]Against the fortified
        citiesAnd against the high corner towers (battlements).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'I will bring distress on menSo that they will walk like the blind
        [unable to find a way of escape],Because they have sinned against the Lord;Their
        blood will be poured out like dust [and trampled underfoot],And their flesh
        like dung.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Neither their silver nor their goldWill be able to rescue themOn
        the day of the Lord\u2019s indignation and wrath.And the whole earth will
        be consumedIn the fire of His jealous wrath,For He shall make a full and
        complete end,Indeed a terrifying one,Of all the inhabitants of the earth."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Judgments on Judah\u2019s Enemies"
      title: "Judgments on Judah\u2019s Enemies"
      number: 1
      content: '  Gather yourselves together [in repentance], yes, gather [in submission],O
        nation without shame,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Before the decree takes effect [and the time for repentance is lost]\u2014The
        day passes like the chaff [whirled by the wind]\u2014Before the burning and
        fierce anger of the Lord comes upon you,Before the day of the wrath of the
        Lord comes upon you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Seek the Lord [search diligently for Him and regard Him as the foremost
        necessity of your life],All you humble of the landWho have practiced His
        ordinances and have kept His commandments;Seek righteousness, seek humility
        [regard them as vital].Perhaps you will be hidden [and pardoned and rescued]In
        the day of the Lord\u2019s anger.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For [this is the fate of the Philistines:] Gaza will be abandonedAnd
        Ashkelon a desolation;[The people of] Ashdod will be driven out at noon [in
        broad daylight]And Ekron will be uprooted and destroyed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Woe (judgment is coming) to the inhabitants of the seacoast,The nation
        of the Cherethites [in Philistia]!The word of the Lord is against you,O Canaan,
        land of the Philistines;I will destroy youSo that no inhabitant will be left.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So the [depopulated] seacoast shall be pastures,With [deserted] meadows
        for shepherds and folds for flocks.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The seacoast will belongTo the remnant of the house of Judah;They
        will pasture [their flocks] on it.In the [deserted] houses of Ashkelon [in
        Philistia] they [of Judah] will lie down and rest in the evening,For the
        Lord their God will care for them;And restore their fortune [permitting them
        to occupy the land].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CI have heard the taunting of MoabAnd the revilings of the sons
        of Ammon,With which they have taunted My peopleAnd become arrogant against
        their territory [by violating Israel\u2019s boundary and trying to seize
        its land].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Therefore, as I live,\u201D declares the Lord of hosts,The God of
        Israel,\u201CMoab will in fact become like SodomAnd the sons of Ammon like
        Gomorrah,A land possessed by nettles and salt pits,And a perpetual desolation.The
        remnant of My people will plunder themAnd what is left of My nation will
        inherit them [as their own].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'This they shall have in return for their pride, because they have
        taunted and become arrogant against the people of the Lord of hosts. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The Lord will be terrifying and awesome to them, for He will starve
        all the gods of the earth; and all the coastlands of the nations will bow
        down and worship Him, everyone from his own place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CYou also, O Ethiopians, will be slain by My sword.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And the Lord will stretch out His hand against the northAnd destroy
        Assyria,And He will make Nineveh a desolation [a wasteland],Parched as the
        desert.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Flocks will lie down in her midst,All the animals which range in
        herds;Both the pelican and the short-eared owlWill roost on the top of Nineveh\u2019s
        pillars.Birds will sing in the window,Desolation will be on the threshold;For
        He has uncovered the cedar paneling.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "This is the joyous cityWhich dwells carelessly [feeling so secure],Who
        says in her heart,\u201CI am, and there is no one besides me.\u201DWhat a
        desolation she has become,A lair for [wild] animals!Everyone who passes by
        her will hiss [in scorn]And wave his hand in contempt."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Woe to Jerusalem and the Nations'
      title: Woe to Jerusalem and the Nations
      number: 1
      content: '  Woe (judgment is coming) to her who is rebellious and defiled,The
        tyrannical city [Jerusalem]!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'She did not listen and heed the voice [of God];She accepted no correction.She
        did not trust in the Lord [but trusted her own power];She did not draw near
        to her God [but to the pagan gods of Baal or Molech].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Her officials within her are roaring lions;Her judges are [as hungry
        as] the wolves at evening,They leave nothing for the morning.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Her prophets are reckless and treacherous men;Her priests have profaned
        the sanctuary;They have done violence to the law [by pretending their word
        is God\u2019s word].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The Lord is righteous within her;He will do no injustice.Every morning
        He brings His justice to light;He does not fail.But the unjust person knows
        no shame.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CI [the Lord] have cut off and destroyed nations [as a warning
        to Judah];Their corner towers (battlements) are in ruins.I have made their
        streets desolateSo that no one passes by;Their cities are destroyedSo that
        there is no man, there is no inhabitant.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "I said, \u2018Most certainly you will [reverently] fear Me;Accept
        correction.\u2019So Jerusalem\u2019s dwelling will not be cut off  In accordance
        with all that I have appointed concerning her [punishment],But they were
        eager [even rising early] to make all their deeds corrupt.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CTherefore [you of the godly remnant of Judah, patiently] wait
        for Me,\u201D declares the Lord,\u201C[Wait] for the day when I rise up as
        a witness [against the nations].For it is My decision and My right to gather
        the nations,To assemble kingdoms,To pour out on them My indignation,All [the
        heat of] My burning anger;For [in that day] all the earth shall be consumedBy
        the fire of My zeal.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then I will give to the peoples [clear and pure speech from] purified
        lips [which reflect their purified hearts],That all of them may call on the
        name of the Lord,To serve Him shoulder to shoulder (united).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'From beyond the rivers of EthiopiaMy worshipers, [the descendants
        of] My dispersed ones,Will bring My offerings.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: A Remnant of Israel'
      title: A Remnant of Israel
      number: 11
      content: 'On that day you [Israel] will feel no shameBecause of all your actsBy
        which you have rebelled and sinned against Me;Then I will remove from among
        youYour rejoicing ones who delight in their pride;And you will never again
        behave arrogantlyOn My holy mountain [Mount Zion].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But I will leave among youA humble and lowly people,And they will
        take refuge and trust confidently in the name of the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "The remnant of Israel will do no wrongNor speak lies,Nor will a deceitful
        tongueBe found in their mouths;For they will eat and lie downWith no one
        to make them tremble and feel afraid.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Shout for joy, O Daughter of Zion!Shout in triumph, O Israel!Rejoice,
        be in high spirits and glory with all your heart,O Daughter of Jerusalem
        [in that day]!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The Lord has taken away the judgments against you;He has cleared
        away your enemies.The King of Israel, even the Lord [Himself], is in your
        midst;You will no longer fear disaster.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "In that day it will be said to Jerusalem:\u201CDo not be afraid,
        O Zion;Do not let your hands fall limp.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The Lord your God is in your midst,A Warrior who saves.He will rejoice
        over you with joy;He will be quiet in His love [making no mention of your
        past sins],He will rejoice over you with shouts of joy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "I will gather those [Israelites in captivity] who grieve about the
        appointed feasts\u2014They came from you, [O Zion];On whom the reproach [of
        exile] is a burden.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Behold, at that time I am going to dealWith all your oppressors;I
        will save the lameAnd gather the scattered,And I will turn their shame into
        praise and renownIn every land [where they have suffered].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "At that time I will bring you in,Yes, at the time I gather you together;For
        I will make you a name and a praiseAmong all the peoples of the earthWhen
        I restore your fortunes [and freedom] before your eyes,\u201DSays the Lord."
      comments: []
